Package: likertr
Title: Analyze Likert Data in One Easy Function
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Lauren", "LaTurner", "lauren.laturner@usu.edu", role = "cre")
    person("Dawson", "Tree", dawson.tree@usu.edu, role = "aut")
    person("Samuel", "Hansen", "a02352588@aggies.usu.edu", role = "aut")
    person("Reagan", "Watrin", "reagan.watrin@usu.edu", role = "aut")
Description: This package takes likert scale data, traditionally used in surveys
    to show direction and magnitude of feeling, and analyses it. The package 
    first cleans the data, then does exploratory factor analysis, finds the 
    consistency of the data, and finally does inference.
